==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[scrifan|scrīfan]], from West Germanic ''*skrīban'', from Latin [[scribere]] ‘write’.  Cognate with Dutch [[schrijven]], German [[schreiben]]; and (''from Latin'') with French [[écrire]], Spanish [[escribir]].

===Pronunciation===
*shrīv, {{IPA|/ʃraɪv/}}, /<tt>SraIv</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪv|Rhymes: -aɪv]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb2|'''shrive'''|'''[[shrives]]'''|'''[[shrove]]'''|'''[[shriven]]'''|'''[[shriving]]'''}}

# ''(transitive and intransitive)'' To hear or receive a confession (of sins etc.)
# ''(transitive)'' To prescribe penance or absolution
# ''(intransitive or reflexive)'' To confess, and receive absolution

